  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a bilingual Greek-and-Latin edition of two ancient philosophical texts on fate, determinism, and free will, printed by Thomas Roycroft in London in 1658. It combines Alexander of Aphrodisias's *De Fato* (On Fate, addressed to the emperors Septimius Severus and Caracalla, c. 198–209 AD) with Ammonius Hermiae's commentary on the second section of Aristotle's *De Interpretatione* (c. 5th century AD). The volume is in duodecimo format with a parchment binding.",
